    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (79.86) and **Andy Pages** (70.96) anchoring the offense. Both benefit immensely from a high-leverage matchup against Chris Paddack; their shared platoon advantage and favorable wind conditions at the park provide the lift necessary to clear the 70-point threshold comfortably. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (68.69) also remains a pillar of reliability today, as he maintains a strong score despite facing a quality arm in Ranger Suarez. His elevated position in the order and positive park factors solidify his role as a daily must-start in our 5x5 build.\n\nStrategic decision-making at the edges remains critical, particularly as we hunt for SB production. **Miguel Vargas** (53.56) earns the start over **Nolan Schanuel** (55.94) despite a slightly lower raw projection, as the optimizer prioritizes the positional flexibility and dynamic baserunning upside **Miguel Vargas** offers against Jack Kochanowicz. While **Nolan Schanuel** was the toughest cut from the bench, his neutral platoon profile against Anthony Kay failed to overcome the threshold set by the current starters. We are actively monitoring a 38% rain risk for both **Miguel Vargas** and **Josh Lowe**; should those games face delays, we remain ready to pivot to bench depth to protect our daily efficiency targets. \n\nFinally, our approach to today's lineup reflects the scarcity of speed, as we are forced to navigate several \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. While **Liam Hicks** (44.05) and **Jackson Merrill** (50.25) face challenging SP_xERAs, their projected roles keep them in the mix. We continue to hold **Gunnar Henderson**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Coby Mayo**, **Brady House**, and **Dominic Smith** in high regard, but given the current constraints, we are maintaining a disciplined rotation to preserve game caps and prioritize the highest daily efficiency scores provided by Steamer.",
